snippet: Rocket fire into Israel continued for a second day, jeopardizing the American-led peace talks and a truce that has held for 16 months.
abstract: Islamic Jihad, militant group responsible for firing dozens of rockets into Israel from the Gaza Strip, says Egypt has intervened to restore calm, offering what appears to be resolution to cross-border violence; Hamas says it is aware of no such truce, pointing to shifting balance of power in region.

byline.contributor: Fares Akram contributed reporting from the Gaza Strip, and David D. Kirkpatrick from Cairo.

lead_paragraph: Rocket fire into Israel continued for a second day, jeopardizing the American-led peace talks and a truce that has held for 16 months.

headline.main: Leaders Deny Report of a Truce in Mideast Violence
headline.print_headline: Leaders Deny Report of a Truce in Mideast Violence
